cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with game theory and optimization problems related to the placement of servers in a network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The paper also involves the study of equilibria and strategy profiles, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of density functions and the analysis of the behavior of the game suggest a connection to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
